1
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,680
-Will it be me, Uncle?
-Yeah, it's going to be you.

2
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:25,960
I only wish
I could go in your place, Idris.

3
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,680
Nah, I don't,
'cause it's really going to hurt.

4
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:32,480
(SIGHS) It's starting.

5
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:38,200
-What will happen?
-Oh.

6
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:42,640
(CLEARING THROAT) Nephew will drain
your mind and your soul from your body

7
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:44,120
and leave your body empty.

8
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:47,640
-I'm scared!
-I expect so, dear.

9
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:50,000
But soon you'll have a new soul.

10
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:51,120
(CHOKING)

11
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,320
There'll be a Time Lord coming!

12
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:57,680
And then we discovered
it wasn't the robot king after all,

13
00:00:57,760 --> 00:00:59,080
it was the real one.

14
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:02,160
Fortunately,
I was able to re-attach the head.

15
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:05,240
-Do you believe any of this stuff?
-I was there.

16
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:07,480
DOCTOR: Oh, it's the warning lights.

17
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,920
I'm getting rid of those.

18
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,400
-They never stop!
-RORY: Hey.

19
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,320
You're still thinking about it,
aren't you?

20
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,640
Oh, shh!

21
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:17,080
We saw him die.

22
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:20,360
-Yeah, 200 years in the future.
-Yes, but it's still going to happen.

23
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,800
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

24
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:24,360
-What was that?
-The door.

25
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,480
It knocked.

26
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:30,080
Right. We are in deep space.

27
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,160
Very, very deep.

28
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,680
(KNOCKING)

29
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:36,480
And somebody's knocking.

30
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,400
Oh, come here.

31
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:48,320
Come here,
you scrumptious little beauty.

32
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,560
-A box?
-Doctor, what is it?

33
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,880
I've got mail.

34
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,720
Time Lord emergency messaging system.

35
00:02:04,800 --> 00:02:07,160
In an emergency, we wrap up
our thoughts in psychic containers

36
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,640
and send them through time and space.

37
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:11,320
Anyway, there's a living Time Lord
still out there

38
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,600
and it's one of the good ones!

39
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,320
You said there weren't
any other Time Lords left.

40
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,680
There are no Time Lords left anywhere
in the universe,

41
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,160
but the universe
isn't where we're going.

42
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:21,720
See that snake? The mark of The Corsair.
Fantastic bloke.

43
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:24,440
He had that snake as a tattoo
in every regeneration.

44
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,400
Didn't feel like himself
unless he had the tattoo.

45
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,800
Or herself, a couple of times.
Ooh, she was a bad girl!

46
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:32,000
Whoa! What is happening?

47
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,680
We are leaving the universe!

48
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:35,160
How can you leave the universe?

49
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,520
With enormous difficulty!

50
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:39,560
Right now I'm burning up Tardis rooms
to give us some welly.

51
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,320
Goodbye, swimming pool.
Goodbye, scullery.

52
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,760
Sayonara, squash court seven!

53
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,200
-(AMY SCREAMING)
-Whoa!

54
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:03,160
Okay. Okay. Where are we?

55
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:07,120
Outside the universe,
where we've never, ever been.

56
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,240
(POWERING DOWN)

57
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,320
Is that meant to be happening?

58
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,760
The power. It's draining.

59
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,840
Everything's draining!
But it can't. That's...

60
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,280
That's impossible.

61
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,240
What is that?

62
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:28,760
It's as if the Matrix, the soul
of the Tardis, has just vanished.

63
00:03:29,240 --> 00:03:30,960
(BEEPING)

64
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,720
Where would it go?

65
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:36,440
(GASPING)

66
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:51,960
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

67
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,760
AMY: So what kind of trouble is
your friend in?

68
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:40,400
DOCTOR: He was in a bind,
a bit of a pickle, sort of distressed.

69
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:42,520
Well, you can just say you don't know.

70
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:45,360
What is this place? The scrapyard
at the end of the universe?

71
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,360
Not end of, outside of.

72
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:51,720
How we can we be outside the universe?
The universe is everything.

73
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,360
Imagine a great big soap bubble

74
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,320
with one of those tiny little bubbles
on the outside.

75
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,120
-Okay.
-But it's nothing like that.

76
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,920
Completely drained, look at her.

77
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,840
Wait.
So we're in a tiny bubble universe,

78
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,680
sticking to the side
of the bigger bubble universe?

79
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:05,720
Yes. No. But if it helps, yes.

80
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,120
This place is full of rift energy.

81
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,840
She'll probably refuel
just by being here.

82
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,760
Now, this place, what do we think, eh?

83
00:05:11,840 --> 00:05:16,240
Gravity's almost Earth-normal,
air's breathable, but it smells like...

84
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:17,440
-Armpits.
-Armpits.

85
00:05:17,520 --> 00:05:19,320
What about all this stuff?
Where did this come from?

86
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,240
Well, there's a rift, now and then
stuff gets sucked through it.

87
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,360
Not a bubble. A plughole.

88
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:24,520
The universe has a plughole
and we've just fallen down it.

89
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:26,480
WOMAN: Thief! Thief! You're my thief!

90
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:29,360
AUNTIE: She's dangerous!
Guard yourself.

91
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:32,080
Look at you! Goodbye! No, not goodbye.
What's the other one?

92
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:35,040
UNCLE: Watch out! Careful.
Keep back from her.

93
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,760
Welcome, strangers, lovely.

94
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,720
-Sorry about the mad person.
-Why am I a thief? What have I stolen?

95
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,560
Me. Are you going to steal me?
No, you have stolen me.

96
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:46,360
You are stealing me. Oh!
Tenses are difficult, aren't they?

97
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:49,400
Oh! Well, we are sorry, my dove.

98
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,600
She's off her head.

99
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:56,760
-They call me Auntie.
-And I'm Uncle. I'm everybody's uncle.

100
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,720
Just keep back from this one, she bites!

101
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,840
-Do I? Excellent. (BITES)
-Ow!

102
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:04,120
-No, no, no!
-Whoa!

103
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,400
-Ow! Ow, ow!
-Oh, biting's excellent!

104
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,080
It's like kissing,
only there's a winner!

105
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:12,440
-Sorry. She's doolally.
-No, I'm not doolally. I'm...

106
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:16,200
I'm... It's on the tip of my tongue.

107
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:19,480
I've just had a new idea about kissing.
Come here, you!

108
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,240
AUNTIE: No, Idris, no!

109
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,840
Oh, but now you're angry.
No, you're not. You will be angry.

110
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,120
The little boxes will make you angry.

111
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:30,760
Sorry? The little what? Boxes?

112
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,880
-(LAUGHING) Your chin is hilarious.
-Oil.

113
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,040
It means the smell of dust after rain.

114
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,280
-What does?
-Petrichor.

115
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,640
But I didn't ask.

116
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,600
Not yet. But you will.

117
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:46,080
AUNTIE: No. No, Idris.
I think you should have a rest.

118
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:49,520
Rest, yes, yes, good idea!
I'll just see if there's an off switch.

119
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,240
ALL: Whoa!

120
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:54,520
Is that it? Is she dead now? So sad.

121
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,840
She's still breathing.

122
00:06:57,080 --> 00:07:02,080
Nephew, take Idris somewhere
she cannot bite people, hmm?

123
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:03,760
Oh, hello!

124
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:05,800
Doctor, what is that?

125
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:08,840
Oh, no. It's all right. It's an Ood.
Oods are good, love an Ood.

126
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,200
Hello, Ood.

127
00:07:10,280 --> 00:07:14,240
Can't you talk?
Oh, I see, it's damaged.

128
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:15,480
May I?

129
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,080
It might be on the wrong frequency.

130
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:22,120
Nephew was broken when he came here.
Why, he was half dead.

131
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:25,760
House repaired him.
House repaired all of us.

132
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,920
MAN: If you are receiving this message,
please help me.

133
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:34,280
Send a signal to the High Council
of the Time Lords on Gallifrey.

134
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:38,200
Tell them that I am still alive!
I don't know where I am.

135
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:41,600
I'm on some rock-like planet.

136
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,720
What was that? Was that him?

137
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:47,880
No, no, it's picking up something else.

138
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:53,240
But that's...
That's not possible. That's...

139
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,760
Who else is here?
Tell me. Show me! Show me!

140
00:07:55,840 --> 00:08:00,440
Just what you see.
It's just the four of us. And the House.

141
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:05,480
Nephew, will you take Idris somewhere
safe where she can't hurt nobody?

142
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,880
The House? What's the House?

143
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:09,800
House is all around you, my sweets.

144
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,880
You are standing on him.

145
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:17,400
This is the House. This world.

146
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,800
Would you like to meet him?

147
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:22,400
-Meet him?
-I'd love to.

148
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:26,680
This way. Come, please. Come.

149
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:29,560
What's wrong? What were those voices?

150
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,480
Time Lords.

151
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,000
It's not just the Corsair.

152
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,360
Somewhere close by
there are lots and lots of...

153
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,680
Time Lords.

154
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,800
IDRIS: I'm...

155
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,480
I'm...

156
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,160
Big word, sad word.

157
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:05,760
Why is that word so sad? No.

158
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,040
Will be sad. Will be sad.

159
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,880
Come. Come, come.

160
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:18,960
Now you can see House
and he can look at you and he...

161
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,440
I see.

162
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,360
This asteroid is sentient.

163
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,600
We walk on his back, breathe his air,
eat his food...

164
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:29,520
-Smell its armpits.
-HOUSE: And do my will.

165
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,840
You are most welcome, travellers.

166
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:36,160
Doctor, that voice,
that's the asteroid talking?

167
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:40,120
Yes. So you're like a sea urchin?

168
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:44,280
Hard outer surface.
That's the planet we're walking on.

169
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:47,080
Big, squashy, oogly thing inside.
That's you.

170
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:49,960
HOUSE: 7hat is correct Time Lord.

171
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:53,880
Ah! So you've met Time Lords before?

172
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:56,240
Many travellers
have come through the rift,

173
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,760
like Auntie and Uncle and Nephew.

174
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,720
I repair them when they break.

175
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:04,920
-So there are Time Lords here, then?
-Not any more.

176
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:09,400
But there have been many Tardises
on my back in days gone by.

177
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:13,160
Well, there won't be any more after us.
Last Time Lord. Last Tardis.

178
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:16,320
A pity. Your people were so kind.

179
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:21,040
Be here in safety, Doctor.
Rest, feed, if you will.

180
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,520
We're not actually going to stay here,
are we?

181
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:28,600
Well, it seems like a friendly planet.
Literally. Mind if we poke around a bit?

182
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:31,760
You can look all you want. Go, look.

183
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,040
House loves you.

184
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:43,840
Come on then, gang.
We're just going to see the sights.

185
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,920
(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

186
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,080
Oh! What was that?
Do fish have fingers?

187
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,800
Like a nine-year-old
trying to rebuild a motorbike.

188
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,840
What am I saying? Why am I saying that?

189
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:08,920
Thief? Where's my thief? Thief!

190
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:13,160
Thief!

191
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,520
(SHUSHING)

192
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,520
So as soon as the Tardis is refuel led,
we go, yeah?

193
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,040
No. There are Time Lords here.
I heard them and they need me.

194
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:23,720
You told me about your people
and you told me what you did.

195
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:25,320
Yes, yes. But if they're like
the Corsair,

196
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,640
they're good ones and I can save them.

197
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,520
And then tell them
you destroyed all the others?

198
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,840
I can explain. Tell them why I had to.

199
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:34,080
You want to be forgiven.

200
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,600
Don't we all?

201
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,000
What do you need from me?

202
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,800
My screwdriver. I left it in the Tardis.
It's in my jacket.

203
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,720
-You're wearing your jacket.
-My other jacket.

204
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,640
-You have two of those?
-Okay. I'll get it.

205
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,120
But Doctor, listen to me.

206
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:55,080
Don't get emotional
because that's when you make mistakes.

207
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,040
-Yes, boss.
-I'll call you from the Tardis.

208
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,920
Rory, look after him.

209
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,760
Rory, look after her.

210
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:04,560
Yeah.

211
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,800
I told you to look after him.

212
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:15,520
He'll be fine. He's a Time Lord.

213
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,160
It's just what they're called.

214
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:18,800
It doesn't mean
he actually knows what he's doing.

215
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:31,880
(MOBILE RINGING)

216
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:34,320
Hey, we're here.
Screwdriver's in your jacket, yeah?

217
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:38,200
Yeah, it's around somewhere.
Have a good look.

218
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,080
(DOOR LOCKS)

219
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:47,000
-Did you do that?
-I didn't do anything.

220
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,560
Right. Jacket.

221
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,200
Come on. Where are you?

222
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:57,160
Now, where are you all? Where are you?

223
00:12:57,280 --> 00:13:00,680
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

224
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,600
Well, they can't all be in here.

225
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:17,520
(DISTANT CHATTERING CONTINUES)

226
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,800
(VOICES CLAMOURING)

227
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:36,160
-Please, do you read me?
-Help!

228
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:39,080
-Please, do you read me?
-Damage to our engines...

229
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:43,320
-Can you hear me? Please respond...
-Contraction and constriction of...

230
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:45,520
(CALLS FOR HELP CONTINUE, OVERLAPPING)

231
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:49,200
Just admiring your Time Lord
distress signal collection.

232
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,120
Nice job. Brilliant job.

233
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,440
Really thought I had some friends here.

234
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,080
But this is what the Ood translator
picked up,

235
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:02,080
cries for help from the long dead.

236
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,840
How many Time Lords have you lured here
the way you lured me?

237
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,040
And what happened to them all?

238
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:16,400
House... House is kind and he is wise.

239
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:20,600
House repairs you when you break!
Yes, I know!

240
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,720
But how does he mend you?

241
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,960
-You've got the eyes of a 20-year-old.
-Thank you.

242
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,560
No. No. I mean it, literally.

243
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,680
Your eyes are 30 years younger
than the rest of you.

244
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,880
Your ears don't match,

245
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,640
your right arm is two inches longer
than your left.

246
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:35,040
And how's your dancing?
'Cause you've got two left feet.

247
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,880
Patchwork people.

248
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,640
You've been repaired
and patched up so often,

249
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,880
I doubt there's anything left
of what used to be you.

250
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,600
I had an umbrella like you once.

251
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:47,800
Oh, now,
it's been a great arm for me, this.

252
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,040
Corsair.

253
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,120
He was a strapping big bloke,
wasn't he, Uncle?

254
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,240
Big fella.

255
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:56,720
I got the arm and then Uncle
got the spine and the kidneys.

256
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,040
Kidneys.

257
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,760
You gave me hope
and then you took it away.

258
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:05,680
That's enough to make anyone dangerous.
God knows what it will do to me.

259
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,240
Basically, run!

260
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,520
Poor old Time Lord. Too late.

261
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:15,880
House is too clever.

262
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:17,560
(MOBILE RINGING)

263
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,600
No sonic screwdriver.

264
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:24,400
Also, the doors seem
to have locked behind us.

265
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:26,360
Rory thinks there is a perfectly
innocent explanation,

266
00:15:26,440 --> 00:15:27,520
but I think you lied to us.

267
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,160
Time Lord stuff.
Needed you out of the way.

268
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,160
What, we're not good enough
for your smart new friends?

269
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:33,000
"Boxes will make you angry."
How could she know?

270
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:36,040
-Doctor, what are you talking about?
-Stay put. Stay exactly where you are.

271
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:39,160
We don't have much...choice.

272
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,840
How did you know about the boxes?
You said they'd make me angry.

273
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,960
-How did you know?
-Ah, it's my thief.

274
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,040
Who are you?

275
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,480
It's about time.

276
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:53,320
He's not trusting us.
And he's being emotional.

277
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,720
This is bad. This is very, very bad.

278
00:15:57,600 --> 00:16:01,200
Yeah. I think it probably is.

279
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:06,080
Sometimes I hate being right.

280
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,600
I don't understand. Who are you?

281
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:10,440
Do you really not know me?
Just because they put me in here?

282
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:14,880
-They said you were dangerous.
-Not the cage, stupid. In here.

283
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,440
They put me in here.

284
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:23,080
I'm the... Oh, what do you call me?

285
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:27,800
We travel. I go... (WHOOSHING)

286
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:31,000
-The Tardis?
-Time and relative dimension in space.

287
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:34,240
Yes, that's it. Names are funny.
It's me!

288
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:37,720
I'm the Tardis.

289
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,760
No, you're not.
You're a bitey mad lady.

290
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,720
The Tardis is up-and-downy stuff
in a big blue box.

291
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:46,520
Yes, that's me. A type 40 Tardis.

292
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,920
I was already a museum piece
when you were young.

293
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,160
And the first time
you touched my console you said...

294
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:55,320
I said you were the most beautiful thing
I had ever known.

295
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:58,720
And then you stole me. And I stole you.

296
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:04,000
I borrowed you.

297
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:07,000
Borrowing implies the eventual intention
to return the thing that was taken.

298
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:10,680
What makes you think
I would ever give you back?

299
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,640
-You're the Tardis?
-Yes.

300
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:22,440
-My Tardis?
-My Doctor.

301
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:27,760
Oh! We have now reached the point in the
conversation where you open the lock.

302
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:46,440
-Are all people like this?
-Like what?

303
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:48,720
So much bigger on the inside?

304
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,640
I'm...

305
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:55,440
Oh, what is that word?
It's so big, so complicated.

306
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:58,320
-And so sad.
-But why?

307
00:17:58,400 --> 00:18:01,560
Why pull the living soul from a Tardis
and pop it in a tiny human head?

308
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:02,680
What does it want you for?

309
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:04,120
-Well, it doesn't want me. (SNIFFS)
-How do you know?

310
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,040
-House eats Tardises.
-House what? What do you mean?

311
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,440
I don't know. Something I heard you say.

312
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,600
-When?
-In the future.

313
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:12,120
-House eats Tardises?
-There you go. What are fish fingers?

314
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:13,680
-When do I say that?
-Any second.

315
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,200
Of course! House feeds on rift energy
and Tardises are bursting with it.

316
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:18,720
And not raw, lovely and cooked,
processed food.

317
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:21,160
-Mmm. Fish fingers.
-Do fish have fingers?

318
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:26,080
But you can't eat a Tardis,
it would destroy you. Unless, unless...

319
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:29,200
Unless you deleted
the Tardis Matrix first.

320
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:32,080
(LAUGHS) So it deleted you.

321
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,880
But House can't just delete
a Tardis consciousness,

322
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,160
that would blow a hole in the universe.

323
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,200
So it pulls out the Matrix,
sticks it into a living receptacle,

324
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:39,280
and it feeds off
the remaining Artron energy.

325
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:40,440
(GASPS)

326
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:44,480
You were about to say all that.
I don't suppose you have to now.

327
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,960
I sent Amy and Rory in there.
They'll be eaten. Amy! Amy!

328
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,800
Rory, get the hell out of there!

329
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,720
-Doctor, something's wrong.
-Yeah. It's House.

330
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,920
He's after the Tardis.
Just get out, both of you!

331
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:58,040
We can't. You locked the door, remember?

332
00:18:58,200 --> 00:18:59,440
But I've unlocked it.

333
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,000
You stupid well haven't!

334
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,800
Doctor, I don't like this.

335
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:08,760
(GRUNTS)

336
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,240
-Open!
-Doctor?

337
00:19:13,640 --> 00:19:15,440
Open this door!

338
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,680
Rory, hold my hand.

339
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:23,640
Amy. Rory!

340
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,880
(WHOOSHING)

341
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:38,960
Amy? Amy, can you hear me?

342
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:43,120
Okay. Right. I don't...

343
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:47,160
I really don't know what to do.

344
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,840
That's a new feeling.

345
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:58,600
Listen, whatever happens,
at least we're together.

346
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:02,080
-And we're in the Tardis, so we're safe.
-Yeah.

347
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:05,480
HOUSE: You're half right.
I mean, you are in the Tardis.

348
00:20:05,560 --> 00:20:07,200
What a great adventure.

349
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,800
I should have done this
half a million years ago.

350
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:13,760
So, Amy, Rory,
why shouldn't I just kill you now?

351
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:20,120
-It's gone.
-Eaten?

352
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,440
No, it left. Not eaten, hijacked.
But why?

353
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:25,280
It's time for us both to go,
Unkie, together.

354
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:28,000
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Go? What do you mean
go? Where are you going?

355
00:20:28,080 --> 00:20:30,000
Well, we're dying, my love.

356
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:32,680
It's time for Auntie and Uncle
to pop off.

357
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:36,600
-I'm against it but...
-It's your fault, isn't it, sweets?

358
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:39,640
'Cause you told House
it was the last Tardis.

359
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:44,120
House can't feed on them
if there's none more coming, can he?

360
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:48,480
So now he's off to your universe
to find more Tardises.

361
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:51,840
-It won't.
-AUNTIE: Oh, it will think of something.

362
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:53,600
(GROANS)

363
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,800
Actually, I feel fine.

364
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,480
Not dead. You can't just die!

365
00:21:01,560 --> 00:21:03,400
We need to go to where I landed, Doctor.
Quickly.

366
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:06,120
-Why?
-Because we are there in three minutes.

367
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,880
We need to go...now!

368
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,160
-Ow!
-What?

369
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:14,040
Roughly how long do these bodies last?

370
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,880
(WHIZZING)

371
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,400
-You're dying.
-Yes, of course I'm dying.

372
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:25,160
I don't belong in a flesh body.
I could blow the casing in no time.

373
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:27,280
No, stop it. Don't get emotional.

374
00:21:27,360 --> 00:21:31,200
Hmm. That's what the orangey girl says.
You're the Doctor. Focus.

375
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:34,920
On what? How?
I'm a madman with a box without a box!

376
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,120
I'm stuck down the plughole
at the end of the universe

377
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,200
on a stupid old junkyard!

378
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,160
-Oh.
-Oh what?

379
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,600
-No, I'm not.
-Not what?

380
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:44,880
'Cause it's not a junkyard.
Don't you see? It's not a junkyard.

381
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,480
-What is it then?
-It's a Tardis junkyard!

382
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:49,440
Come on! Oh, sorry, do you have a name?

383
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,080
Seven hundred years, finally he asks.

384
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:52,840
-So what do I call you?
-I think you call me...

385
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:54,800
Sexy.

386
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,280
Only when we're alone!

387
00:21:58,560 --> 00:21:59,640
We are alone.

388
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:02,400
Oh. Come on, then, Sexy.

389
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:10,160
HOUSE: Corridors. I have corridors.
So much to learn about my new home.

390
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:12,960
But you haven't answered
my question, children.

391
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:15,360
Uh, question?

392
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:20,080
You remember. Tell me why
I shouldn't just kill you both now?

393
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:24,000
Well, because... Rory, why?

394
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,440
Because

395
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,800
killing us quickly wouldn't be any fun.

396
00:22:33,320 --> 00:22:35,480
And you need fun, don't you?

397
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:38,840
That's what Auntie and Uncle were for,
wasn't it? Someone to make suffer.

398
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:41,320
I had a PE teacher just like you.

399
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,400
You need to be entertained

400
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:49,480
and killing us quickly
wouldn't be entertainment.

401
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:52,600
So entertain me. Run.

402
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:10,480
DOCTOR: A valley of half-eaten Tardises.
You thinking what I'm thinking?

403
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,120
I'm thinking that
all of my sisters are dead,

404
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:17,080
that they were devoured and that
we are looking at their corpses.

405
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:19,360
Ah. Sorry. No, I wasn't thinking that.

406
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:23,480
No. You were thinking you could build
a working Tardis console

407
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,160
out of broken remnants
of 100 different models.

408
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,320
And you don't care that it's impossible.

409
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:30,280
DOCTOR: It's not impossible
as long as we're alive.

410
00:23:30,360 --> 00:23:34,560
Rory and Amy need me.
So, yeah. We're going to build a Tardis.

411
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,720
So are we having fun yet?

412
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:51,680
I'm rather enjoying the sensation
of having you running around inside me.

413
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:53,200
-(SCREAMS)
-No!

414
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:57,520
I've turned off the corridor
anti-grav, so do be careful.

415
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,400
Come on.

416
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:07,200
(GRUNTS)

417
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,680
Whoa!

418
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:19,440
Bond the tube directly
into the tachyon diverter.

419
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:22,000
Yes, I have actually rebuilt a Tardis
before, you know.

420
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:23,120
I know what I'm doing.

421
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,720
You're like a nine-year-old trying to
rebuild a motorbike in his bedroom.

422
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,080
And you never read the instructions.

423
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,920
-I always read the instructions!
-There's a sign on my front door.

424
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,680
You have been walking past it
for 700 years. What does it say?

425
00:24:32,760 --> 00:24:34,280
That's not instructions!

426
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,240
There's an instruction at the bottom.
What does it say?

427
00:24:36,320 --> 00:24:37,800
-"Pull to open.”
-Yes. And what do you do?

428
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:40,480
-I push!
-Every single time. 700 years.

429
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:42,600
Police box doors open out the way.

430
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:46,640
I think I have earned the right
to open my front doors any way I want.

431
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:50,080
Your front doors? Have you any idea
how childish that sounds?

432
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,920
-You are not my mother.
-And you are not my child.

433
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
You know,
since we're talking with mouths,

434
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:57,200
not really an opportunity
that comes along very often,

435
00:24:57,280 --> 00:25:01,320
I just want to say, you know,
you have never been very reliable.

436
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,720
And you have?

437
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:04,120
You didn't always take me
where I wanted to go.

438
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:07,360
No, but I always took you
where you needed to go.

439
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:09,800
You did.

440
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,680
Look at us. Talking! Wouldn't it
be amazing if we could always talk?

441
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,960
Even when you're stuck inside the box?

442
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,000
But you know
I'm not constructed that way.

443
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,240
I exist across all space and time

444
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:21,000
and you talk and run around
and bring home strays.

445
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:22,720
(GROANS)

446
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:27,640
You okay?

447
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:31,120
One of the kidneys has already failed.

448
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:34,200
It doesn't matter. We need to finish
assembling the console.

449
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:38,040
Using a console without a proper shell.
It's not going to be safe.

450
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,880
This body has about
18 minutes left to live.

451
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:43,080
The universe we're in
will reach absolute zero in three hours.

452
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:44,520
Safe is relative.

453
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:49,520
Then we need to get a move on, eh,
old girl?

454
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:02,400
No!

455
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:05,840
-Amy!
-No!

456
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:07,280
(GRUNTING)

457
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:08,840
Amy!

458
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,480
RORY: Amy.

459
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:14,640
Amy!

460
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:18,400
Amy!

461
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,760
Rory?

462
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:26,240
Where have you been?

463
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:28,000
I stepped through that door
and it came back here.

464
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,840
-But you've been hours.
-No, I haven't.

465
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,840
It's House,
and it's messing with the Tardis.

466
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,520
Come on, walk this way.

467
00:26:41,280 --> 00:26:43,480
-No!
-No! Oh!

468
00:26:48,760 --> 00:26:50,880
You'll need to install the time rotor.

469
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:53,760
DOCTOR: Well, how is this
going to make it through the rift? How?

470
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:58,960
We're almost done. Thrust diff user.

471
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:02,960
-Ah, retroscope. Blue thingy.
-Oh, Doctor.

472
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,800
Do you ever wonder why I chose you
all those years ago?

473
00:27:05,880 --> 00:27:08,760
-I chose you. You were unlocked.
-Of course I was.

474
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:12,240
I wanted to see the universe,
so I stole a Time Lord and I ran away.

475
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:13,760
And you were the only one mad enough.

476
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:17,160
Right. Perfect. Look at that.
What could possibly go wrong?

477
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:21,120
That's fine. That always happens.
No! Hang on. Wait.

478
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,760
RORY: Amy?

479
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:40,240
Oh, my God.

480
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:42,440
Rory?

481
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:46,480
You left me. How could you do that?
How could you leave me?

482
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:48,960
How long have you been here?

483
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:52,320
Two thousand years I waited for you!
You did it to me again!

484
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:55,200
I didn't mean to. I didn't mean to.
I'm sorry.

485
00:27:55,280 --> 00:27:56,320
(SCREAMS)

486
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,760
Rory, what are you doing?

487
00:27:58,320 --> 00:27:59,720
They come for me at night.

488
00:28:00,200 --> 00:28:03,320
Every single night,
they come for me and they hurt me.

489
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:08,800
Amy, they hurt me over and over
and over and over...

490
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:12,040
-Rory.
-(SHOUTING) How could you leave me?

491
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:15,440
How could you do that to me?

492
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:21,240
Right. Okay, let's go.

493
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:23,520
Follow that Tardis!

494
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,080
(POWERING DOWN)

495
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:28,640
Oh, no, come on. There's rift energy
everywhere, you can do it.

496
00:28:28,720 --> 00:28:32,320
Okay, diverting all power to thrust.
Let's be having you.

497
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:33,880
(ELECTRICITY SURGING)

498
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,800
-No, no, no, no!
-What's wrong?

499
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:39,040
It can't hold the charge.
I can't even start. There's no power!

500
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:41,200
Will you...

501
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:44,080
I've got nothing!

502
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:46,480
Oh, my beautiful idiot.

503
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:49,000
You have what you've always had.

504
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,960
You've got me.

505
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:57,680
(WHOOSHING)

506
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:12,800
(GASPS)

507
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,440
(AMY SHUDDERING)

508
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:26,680
No! No!

509
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:30,280
(SOBBING)

510
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:32,880
Rory.

511
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,480
I'm so, so sorry!

512
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:43,160
-Amy?
-(GASPS)

513
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:56,400
It's messing with our heads.
Come on, run.

514
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:05,600
-Whoo-hoo!
-We've locked on to them!

515
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:09,560
They'll have to lower the shields
when we're close enough to phase inside!

516
00:30:09,920 --> 00:30:14,360
Can you get a message to Amy?
The telepathic circuits are online!

517
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:18,040
Which one's Amy? The pretty one?

518
00:30:18,960 --> 00:30:20,040
(GROANS)

519
00:30:20,120 --> 00:30:22,640
-Rory, what's wrong?
-It's like I'm getting a message.

520
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:23,920
Hello, pretty!

521
00:30:24,640 --> 00:30:25,840
What the hell is that?

522
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:29,960
Don't worry. Telepathic messaging.
No, that's Rory.

523
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:33,800
You have to go to the old control room.
I'm putting the route in your head.

524
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,040
When you get there,

525
00:30:35,120 --> 00:30:38,040
use the purple slider on
the nearest panel to lower the shields.

526
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:40,720
-The pretty one?
-You'll have about 12 seconds

527
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:43,640
before the room goes into phase
with the invading Matrix.

528
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:46,600
I'll send you the passkey
when you get there. Good luck.

529
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:48,680
What was that?

530
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:52,720
It was that woman.
That mad woman and the Doctor.

531
00:30:53,040 --> 00:30:54,800
-The Doctor?
-We have to keep going.

532
00:30:56,840 --> 00:30:59,280
How's he going to be able
to take down the shields anyway?

533
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:01,080
The House is in the control room!

534
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,400
I directed him
to one of the old control rooms.

535
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:06,680
There aren't any old control rooms!
They were all deleted or remodel led!

536
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:10,440
I archive them! For neatness!
I've got about 30 now!

537
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:13,360
But I've only changed the desktop,
what, a dozen times?

538
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:15,120
So far, yes!

539
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:17,960
You can't archive something
that hasn't happened yet!

540
00:31:18,240 --> 00:31:19,400
You can't.

541
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:25,640
(AMY GASPS)

542
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,080
What happened to the lights?

543
00:31:28,560 --> 00:31:30,000
The lights are fine.

544
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:33,160
It's messing with our heads again.

545
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:44,040
-(WHISPERING) Okay. Stay there a second.
-What is it? What?

546
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:46,040
Just hang on.

547
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:50,000
Don't leave me.
I can hardly see, you idiot!

548
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:51,560
(RORY SCREAMS)

549
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:53,720
Rory?

550
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,200
-Rory?
-RORY: It's okay.

551
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:58,320
(AMY SIGHS)

552
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:01,240
I'm fine. Come towards my voice.

553
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:04,960
AMY: What happened? Where are you?

554
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:08,680
RORY: I just banged my head.
Just keep coming.

555
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,800
Reach out your hand.

556
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:29,880
This way. Come on, run!

557
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:34,480
Keep going!
You're doing it, You Sexy Thing!

558
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:37,280
See, you do call me that.
Is it my name?

559
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:40,120
-You bet it's your name!
-Whoo!

560
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,400
(DOCTOR GROANING)

561
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:50,600
I can see. Now, Rory, I can see.

562
00:32:50,680 --> 00:32:52,480
That was the Ood thing, the Nephew,
and it's still coming.

563
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:54,960
I know. So where is this place?

564
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:57,880
This is where she told me to go.
She said she'd send me the passkey!

565
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,200
(GROANS)

566
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:03,600
-Crimson. Eleven. Delight. Petrichor.
-Crimson. Eleven. Delight. Petrichor.

567
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,840
-Petrichor.
-What do I do, do I say it?

568
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:09,560
Crimson. Eleven. Delight. Petrichor.

569
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:12,880
I said it.

570
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,680
-Petrichor. Petrichor.
-I said it!

571
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:16,080
Petrichor.

572
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:20,000
She told you what it meant.
The smell of wet dust, remember? So...

573
00:33:20,080 --> 00:33:21,320
Always the meaning, not the word.

574
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,320
-The meaning of what?
-The Tardis interface is telepathic.

575
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:24,440
You don't say it, you think it.

576
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:26,120
-It's coming.
-Quiet!

577
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:31,800
(WHISPERING) Crimson. Eleven. Delight.

578
00:33:32,320 --> 00:33:34,480
And the smell of dust after rain.

579
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:39,160
Crimson. Eleven. Delight.
The smell of dust after rain.

580
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:42,920
Crimson. Eleven. Delight.
The smell of dust after rain.

581
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,800
What is this place?

582
00:33:48,520 --> 00:33:50,320
Another control room?

583
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:52,280
RORY: Right, shields.

584
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,440
(CONTROLS BEEPING)

585
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:55,720
Got it.

586
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:01,120
They did it! Shields down.

587
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:08,960
HOUSE: How did you find this place?
It's not on my internal schematics.

588
00:34:09,560 --> 00:34:12,920
I had hoped you two could join Nephew
as my servants.

589
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:16,360
But you two are nothing but trouble.

590
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,160
Nephew,

591
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,600
kill them.

592
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:29,320
(GROANS)

593
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,240
We're coming through!

594
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:33,080
Get out of the way
or you'll be atomised!

595
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,600
-Where are you coming through?
-I don't know!

596
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:37,360
Oh, great. Thanks.

597
00:34:41,320 --> 00:34:43,720
-(DOCTOR GROANS)
-It's not going to hold!

598
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,120
Hold on!

599
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,040
(SCREAMING)

600
00:34:58,560 --> 00:34:59,760
Doctor.

601
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:02,960
(AMY CHUCKLES)

602
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:05,840
Not good. Not good at all.

603
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:11,800
-How do you walk around in these things?
-Well, we're not quite there yet.

604
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:15,640
Just hold on. Amy, this is...

605
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:18,720
Well, she's my Tardis.

606
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:23,520
Except she's a woman.
She's a woman and she's my Tardis.

607
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,880
-She's the Tardis?
-And she's a woman.

608
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:29,440
She's a woman and she's the Tardis.

609
00:35:29,520 --> 00:35:31,600
Did you wish really hard?

610
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:33,680
Shut up! Not like that.

611
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,240
Hello. I'm...

612
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:38,800
-Sexy.
-Oh! Still shut up.

613
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:40,920
HOUSE: 7he environment
has been breached.

614
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:43,000
Nephew, kill them all.

615
00:35:43,960 --> 00:35:45,000
Where's Nephew?

616
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:46,760
He was standing
right where you materialised.

617
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,920
Ah! Well, he must have
been redistributed.

618
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:51,040
-Meaning what?
-You're breathing him.

619
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:52,400
(EXCLAIMS IN DISGUST)

620
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:54,400
Another Ood I failed to save.

621
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:57,560
Doctor, I did not expect you.

622
00:35:57,640 --> 00:36:01,760
Well, that's me all over, isn't it?
Lovely old unexpected me.

623
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:05,600
The big question is now you're here,
how to dispose of you?

624
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:06,920
I could play with gravity...

625
00:36:07,680 --> 00:36:09,120
(ALL GASPING)

626
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,080
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

627
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:17,360
Or I could evacuate the air
from this room and watch you choke.

628
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,280
(AIR WHOOSHING)

629
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,280
(ALL GASPING)

630
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:24,320
You really don't want to do that!

631
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:26,440
Why shouldn't I just kill you now?

632
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:29,640
Because then I won't be able
to help you! Listen to your engines.

633
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:32,280
Just listen to them. You don't have
the thrust and you know it.

634
00:36:32,360 --> 00:36:34,000
Right now I'm your only hope

635
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:36,880
for getting out of your little bubble
through the rift and into my universe.

636
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:39,040
-And mine's the one with the food in!
-(GASPING) Water...

637
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:43,480
You just have to promise not to kill us.
That's all. Just promise.

638
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:46,240
-You can't be serious.
-I'm very serious.

639
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,000
I'm sure it's an entity of its word.

640
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:50,400
RORY: Doctor, she's burning up.
She's asking for water.

641
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:56,840
Hey. Hang in there, old girl.

642
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,520
Not long now. It'll be over soon.

643
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:05,320
I always liked it
when you called me "old girl".

644
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:09,600
You want me to give my word?
Easy. I promise.

645
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,640
Fine. Okay. I trust you.

646
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:15,720
Just delete, ooh,
30% of the Tardis rooms,

647
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,760
you'll free up thrust
enough to make it through.

648
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,680
Activate sub-routine sigma nine.

649
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:23,160
Why would you tell me this?

650
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:25,880
Because we want to get back
to our universe as badly as you do.

651
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:27,520
And I'm nice.

652
00:37:27,600 --> 00:37:30,280
Yes. I can delete rooms

653
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:35,240
and I can also rid myself of vermin
if I delete this room first.

654
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:37,720
Thank you, Doctor, very helpful.

655
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:41,960
Goodbye, Time Lord.
Goodbye, little humans. Goodbye, Idris.

656
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,760
(WHOOSHING)

657
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,840
Yes. I mean you could do that,
but it just won't work.

658
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:05,960
Hardwired fail-safe.

659
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,440
Living things
from rooms that are deleted

660
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:10,000
are automatically deposited
in the main control room.

661
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:11,200
But thanks for the Lift.

662
00:38:11,280 --> 00:38:13,240
We are in your universe now, Doctor.

663
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:15,880
Why should it matter to me
in which room you die?

664
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:18,840
I can kill you just as easily here
as anywhere.

665
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:22,000
Fear me.
I've killed hundreds of Time Lords.

666
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:24,480
Fear me. I've killed all of them.

667
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:26,880
I don't understand.
There isn't a forest in here.

668
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:29,880
Yeah, you're right.
You've completely won.

669
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:33,160
Oh, you can kill us
in oodles of really inventive ways,

670
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:36,400
but before you do kill us,
allow me and friends Amy and Rory

671
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:40,160
to congratulate you
on being an absolutely worthy opponent.

672
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,640
Congratulations.

673
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:49,960
Yep, you've defeated us,
me and my lovely friends here,

674
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:53,040
and last but definitely not least,
the Tardis Matrix herself,

675
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:57,120
a living consciousness
you ripped out of this very control room

676
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,280
and locked up into a human body,
and look at her.

677
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:00,720
Doctor, she's stopped breathing.

678
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:04,040
-Enough! That is enough.
-No. It's never enough!

679
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:06,040
You forced the Tardis into a body

680
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:09,520
so she'd burn out safely a very long way
away from this control room.

681
00:39:09,760 --> 00:39:12,240
A flesh body
can't hold the Tardis Matrix and live.

682
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,400
Look at her body, House.

683
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:16,440
And you think I should mourn her?

684
00:39:16,520 --> 00:39:17,560
No.

685
00:39:18,600 --> 00:39:21,600
I think you should be very, very careful

686
00:39:21,680 --> 00:39:24,720
about what you let back
into this control room.

687
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:27,280
You took her from her home.

688
00:39:28,160 --> 00:39:31,640
But now she's back in the box again
and she's free!

689
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:36,320
No! Doctor, stop this!

690
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:39,400
Ah! Stop this now!

691
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:42,240
Look at my girl, look at her go!

692
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:44,720
Bigger on the inside!

693
00:39:45,320 --> 00:39:46,880
-You see, House?
-Make her stop!

694
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,320
-That's your problem.
-(HOUSE GROANING)

695
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:52,000
The size of a planet,
but inside you are just so small.

696
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:54,200
Make it stop!

697
00:39:54,400 --> 00:39:56,200
Finish him off, girl.

698
00:39:56,440 --> 00:39:58,760
HOUSE: (GROANING) Don't do this!

699
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:03,520
(HOUSE SCREAMING)

700
00:40:07,880 --> 00:40:11,000
IDRIS: (ECHOING) Doctor? Are you there?

701
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:13,800
It's so very dark in here.

702
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:17,200
I'm here.

703
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:25,840
I've been looking for a word.

704
00:40:27,440 --> 00:40:30,760
A big, complicated word, but so sad.

705
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:34,400
I've found it now.

706
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:37,280
What word?

707
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:39,600
Alive.

708
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:43,240
I'm alive!

709
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,600
Alive isn't sad.

710
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:48,160
It's sad when it's over.

711
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,680
I'll always be here.

712
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:54,000
But this is when we talked.

713
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,200
And now even that has come to an end.

714
00:41:00,080 --> 00:41:02,760
There's something
I didn't get to say to you.

715
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:06,760
Goodbye?

716
00:41:06,840 --> 00:41:10,480
No, I just wanted to say...

717
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:13,360
hello.

718
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:17,160
Hello, Doctor.

719
00:41:19,040 --> 00:41:21,560
It's so very, very nice to meet you.

720
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:27,320
Please.

721
00:41:29,720 --> 00:41:31,480
I don't want you to.

722
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:34,360
Please.

723
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:40,440
(WHOOSHING)

724
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:43,360
I love you.

725
00:41:46,960 --> 00:41:49,040
Where? (SNIFFING)

726
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:10,080
How's it going under there?

727
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:13,960
Yeah. Just putting a firewall
around the Matrix. Almost done.

728
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:17,320
-Are you going to make her talk again?
-Can't.

729
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:19,520
-Why not?
-Spacey-wacey, isn't it?

730
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:21,800
Well, actually, it's because
the Time Lords discovered that

731
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:25,480
if you take an 11th-dimensional Matrix
and fold it into a mechanical, then...

732
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:28,840
Yes, it's spacey-wacey!

733
00:42:30,360 --> 00:42:33,720
Sorry. At the end, she was talking.
She kept repeating something.

734
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:36,280
-I don't know what it meant.
-What did she say?

735
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:39,080
"The only water in the forest
is the river."

736
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:40,920
She said we'd need to know that someday.

737
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,800
-It doesn't make sense, does it?
-Not yet.

738
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:47,560
-You okay?
-No.

739
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:51,920
I watched her die. I shouldn't
let it get to me, but it still does.

740
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:54,400
I'm a nurse.

741
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:56,880
Letting it get to you,
you know what that's called?

742
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:59,200
Being alive. Best thing there is.

743
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:02,400
Being alive right now
is all that counts.

744
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:05,360
Nearly finished.
Two more minutes, then we're off.

745
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:07,440
The Eye of Orion's restful,
if you like restful.

746
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,800
I can never
really get the hang of restful.

747
00:43:09,880 --> 00:43:12,920
What do you think, dear?
Where shall we take the kids this time?

748
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:16,160
Look at you pair.
It's always you and her, isn't it?

749
00:43:16,240 --> 00:43:17,640
Long after the rest of us have gone.

750
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:20,600
A boy and his box,
off to see the universe.

751
00:43:20,760 --> 00:43:22,880
Well, you say that
as if it's a bad thing.

752
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:24,840
But honestly,
it's the best thing there is.

753
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:27,760
The House deleted all the bedrooms.

754
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:29,080
I should probably make you two
a new bedroom.

755
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,640
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

756
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:31,880
(AMY AND RORY TALKING QUIETLY)

757
00:43:31,960 --> 00:43:35,440
Okay, um, Doctor, this time
could we lose the bunk beds?

758
00:43:35,520 --> 00:43:39,080
No, bunk beds are cool.
A bed with a ladder.

759
00:43:40,120 --> 00:43:41,880
You can't beat that.

760
00:43:42,640 --> 00:43:43,920
It's your room.

761
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,560
Up those stairs, keep walking
till you find it. Off you pop.

762
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:51,040
Doctor, do you have a room?

763
00:44:18,200 --> 00:44:19,680
Are you there?

764
00:44:21,280 --> 00:44:22,880
Can you hear me?

765
00:44:25,400 --> 00:44:27,320
No. I'm a silly old...

766
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:30,840
Okay. The Eye of Orion,
or wherever we need to go.

767
00:44:35,080 --> 00:44:36,240
Hello!

768
00:44:37,800 --> 00:44:39,120
(LAUGHING)

769
00:44:41,120 --> 00:44:43,280
Whoo-hoo!

770
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:56,520
(SCREAMING)

771
00:44:57,920 --> 00:44:58,920
(SCREAMING)

772
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:04,000
WOMAN: The flesh.
It's fully programmable matter.

773
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:07,640
It acts like life, but it still needs
to be controlled by us.

774
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:11,880
MAN: They can't remain stable
without us plumbed into them.

775
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:16,080
Trust me. I'm the Doctor.

776
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:17,200
(HISSES)

